'''帕什米纳'''指的是一种精细的羊绒羊毛和由它制成的纺织物的统称，这种纺织物起源于印度<ref name="LuxFib">{{cite book|last= Franck|first= Robert R.|title= Silk, Mohair, Cashmere and Other Luxury Fibres|url= http://books.google.com/books?id=M-om7HI3rwcC&pg=PA142&vq=pashmina&dq=cashmere+pashmina|accessdate= 2008-07-08|date= October 2001|publisher= Woodhead Publishing|isbn= 1-85573-540-7|page= 142|archive-date= 2017-03-24|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170324020321/https://books.google.com/books?id=M-om7HI3rwcC&pg=PA142&vq=pashmina&dq=cashmere+pashmina|dead-url= no}}</ref><ref name="OED">"Pashmina." ''The Oxford English Dictionary''. 2nd ed. 1989.</ref>。该名字来源于“Pashmineh”，在波斯语中来自“Pashm”，意思是“[[羊毛|羊毛]]” <ref name="OED"/>。这种羊毛来自于一种叫做changthangi或者Pashmina的山羊，这种山羊是由Mir Sayyid Ali Hamadani首次在[[拉達克|拉达克地区]]发现的，属于[[山羊|山羊]]的一种特殊品种，生活在[[印度|印度]]、[[尼泊尔|尼泊尔]]和[[巴基斯坦|巴基斯坦]]的[[喜马拉雅山|喜马拉雅山]]脉地区。帕什米纳披肩则是指利用手工纺线，编织并且刺绣的一种纺织品，通常是在尼泊尔和[[克什米尔|克什米尔]]地区，并且由细山羊绒纤维制成<ref name="LuxFib"/><ref name="LuxKnit">{{cite book |last=Morse |first=Linda |author2=Lidia Karabinech |author3=Lina Perl |author4=Colby Brin |title=Luxury Knitting: The Ultimate Guide to Exquisite Yarns |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=r2N05Gz_FUsC&pg=PA12&dq=cashmere+pashmina#PPA12,M1 |accessdate=2008-07-08 |date=October 2005 |publisher=Sterling Publishing |isbn=1-931543-86-0 |page=12 |archive-date=2020-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206070057/https://books.google.com/books?id=r2N05Gz_FUsC&pg=PA12&dq=cashmere+pashmina#PPA12,M1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

